  "hub.helpSq": "Click a piece in the tray: it appears in the centre. Then drag it wherever you like. ⟳ turns it, ⇄ flips it, Delete removes it. Close a fence: you enclose an area.",
  "hub.helpHex": "Click a piece in the tray: it appears in the centre of the honeycomb. Then drag it wherever you like. ⟳ turns it, ⇄ flips it, Delete removes it. Close a fence: you enclose an area.",
  "hub.helpTri": "Click a piece in the tray: it appears in the centre of the field. Then drag it wherever you like. ⟳ turns it, ⇄ flips it, Delete removes it. Close a fence: you enclose an area.",
  "hub.infoSq": "The five free tetrominoes — i, l, n, o, t — each once. \"Free\" means a mirror image is the same piece. Challenge 1 of the paper.",
  "hub.infoHex": "Four free tetrahexes — four hexagons joined — arc, bar, wave and worm, each once. The lab it opens, Challenge 3, uses all seven.",
  "hub.infoTri": "Three hexiamonds — six triangles joined — each once. On this tiling, two triangles that touch only at a corner still count as connected, so the fence must close the corners too. The lab it opens, Challenge 4, uses all twelve.",
