  "hub.areaTip": "Area currently enclosed on your board",
  "hub.coinSqTip": "On the square tiling, two cells can touch at a vertex without sharing an edge. If your fence closes only through such a vertex, the outside slips through — the corner encloses nothing. This indicator lights up when that happens on your board.",
  "hub.coinLabel": "corner",
  "hub.coinOpen": "corner open",
  "hub.coinHexTip": "On the hex tiling, 3 hexes meet at each vertex and are pairwise edge-adjacent. So \"leak through a corner\" implies \"leak through an edge\". Impossible.",
